      "message": "I\u0027m wondering if rather than configuring key-value data on the local machine, we should just proxy metadata requests to a \"skolo\" GCE project. E.g. if this server gets a request for \"/computeMetadata/v1/project/attributes/{key}\", it would in turn query \"https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/skolo/attributes/{key}\".\n\nThis wouldn\u0027t work for instance metadata, unless we want to map that to specially-formatted project-level metadata.\n\nAnother option would be to store key-value data in GCS (with caching).",
